>>EDWARDS: On the other
side of grief is joy.

00:43:00.840 --> 00:43:02.570 align:middle line:84%
So in your mind's
eye right now, I just

00:43:02.570 --> 00:43:05.690 align:middle line:84%
want you to think of
something that brings you joy.

00:43:05.690 --> 00:43:08.210 align:middle line:90%
A person, an animal, a place.

00:43:08.210 --> 00:43:09.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:43:09.170 --> 00:43:09.440 align:middle line:90%
My daughter.

00:43:09.440 --> 00:43:11.540 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: Visualize,
you got it in your heart?

00:43:11.540 --> 00:43:11.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:43:11.930 --> 00:43:12.140 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: You got that?

00:43:12.140 --> 00:43:14.318 align:middle line:84%
Well, blow it right
into that stone.

00:43:14.318 --> 00:43:16.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [EXHALING]

00:43:16.710 --> 00:43:18.610 align:middle line:90%
She makes me laugh.

00:43:18.610 --> 00:43:22.110 align:middle line:90%
[EXHALING]

00:43:22.110 --> 00:43:25.110 align:middle line:90%


00:43:25.110 --> 00:43:26.460 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: OK.

00:43:26.460 --> 00:43:30.780 align:middle line:84%
So take all these stones and
put them up to your heart.

00:43:30.780 --> 00:43:31.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:43:31.880 --> 00:43:36.710 align:middle line:84%
It's joy and grief and
empowerment and voice.

00:43:36.710 --> 00:43:38.450 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: And voice.

00:43:38.450 --> 00:43:41.780 align:middle line:84%
And hold them to
your heart, and just

00:43:41.780 --> 00:43:44.054 align:middle line:84%
breathe through
your heart a bit.

00:43:44.054 --> 00:43:46.826 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [EXHALING]

00:43:46.826 --> 00:43:48.220 align:middle line:90%


00:43:48.220 --> 00:43:51.370 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: This is the way
you love yourself, Lisa.

00:43:51.370 --> 00:43:55.750 align:middle line:84%
This is the way you love
yourself first, and then share

00:43:55.750 --> 00:44:02.080 align:middle line:84%
it, by holding
yourself in your heart.

00:44:02.080 --> 00:44:06.452 align:middle line:90%


00:44:06.452 --> 00:44:07.712 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:44:07.712 --> 00:44:08.920 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: That's no regrets.

00:44:08.920 --> 00:44:10.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's beautiful.

00:44:10.900 --> 00:44:12.430 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Isn't that wonderful?

00:44:12.430 --> 00:44:15.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I can feel
all of the people

00:44:15.100 --> 00:44:20.710 align:middle line:84%
that are thinking about their
regrets of the end of life

00:44:20.710 --> 00:44:25.730 align:middle line:84%
with their loved ones, and how
it's possible to release those.

00:44:25.730 --> 00:44:26.530 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Right.

00:44:26.530 --> 00:44:27.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:44:27.670 --> 00:44:29.378 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: You can
take these stones home

00:44:29.378 --> 00:44:31.420 align:middle line:84%
and share them with
your loved ones.

00:44:31.420 --> 00:44:33.605 align:middle line:84%
There are other stones
for the other practices.

00:44:33.605 --> 00:44:35.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because they'll watch
this show, and then they'll

00:44:35.980 --> 00:44:37.150 align:middle line:90%
understand what they mean.

00:44:37.150 --> 00:44:38.390 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: There you go.

00:44:38.390 --> 00:44:39.190 align:middle line:90%
There you go.

00:44:39.190 --> 00:44:40.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Which is amazing.

00:44:40.390 --> 00:44:42.390 align:middle line:10%
>>EDWARDS: And the other
thing we have in here--

00:44:42.390 --> 00:44:44.150 align:middle line:10%
and you can take
this home, too--

00:44:44.150 --> 00:44:46.810 align:middle line:10%
we have a little
lotus flower altar.

00:44:46.810 --> 00:44:50.140 align:middle line:84%
And you can create your
own ritual around it.

00:44:50.140 --> 00:44:53.275 align:middle line:10%
It has the practices
inside of it.

00:44:53.275 --> 00:44:54.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, I love this.

00:44:54.700 --> 00:44:56.510 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: Be
grateful every day.

00:44:56.510 --> 00:44:57.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:44:57.310 --> 00:44:58.430 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Trust, take the risk.

00:44:58.430 --> 00:45:01.030 align:middle line:84%
So if you're going to take a
risk, you know, step in there

00:45:01.030 --> 00:45:02.020 align:middle line:90%
and trust it.

00:45:02.020 --> 00:45:05.020 align:middle line:84%
Have the courage to
be me, and choose joy.

00:45:05.020 --> 00:45:09.060 align:middle line:10%
But in the center
is love myself--

00:45:09.060 --> 00:45:10.270 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: And share it.

00:45:10.270 --> 00:45:10.540 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: --and share it.

00:45:10.540 --> 00:45:11.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, this is beautiful.

00:45:11.790 --> 00:45:17.560 align:middle line:84%
What a wonderful gift to
give someone who is grieving.

00:45:17.560 --> 00:45:20.060 align:middle line:90%
Because again, it's--

00:45:20.060 --> 00:45:24.490 align:middle line:84%
I know I keep saying this, but
it gives purpose to grieving.

00:45:24.490 --> 00:45:26.576 align:middle line:90%
It gives motion.

00:45:26.576 --> 00:45:27.410 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Mhm.

00:45:27.410 --> 00:45:28.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Motion.

00:45:28.110 --> 00:45:29.440 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: Well, this
is why we use breath.

00:45:29.440 --> 00:45:29.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:45:29.910 --> 00:45:30.990 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: That's
not accidental.

00:45:30.990 --> 00:45:31.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That helped.

00:45:31.310 --> 00:45:32.820 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: This is the energy.

00:45:32.820 --> 00:45:33.820 align:middle line:90%
And we use stones--

00:45:33.820 --> 00:45:36.340 align:middle line:84%
this is from Peru, the
high mountains of Peru--

00:45:36.340 --> 00:45:39.790 align:middle line:84%
because stones
hold wisdom for us.

00:45:39.790 --> 00:45:42.310 align:middle line:84%
So you don't have to remember
which is the lodestone

00:45:42.310 --> 00:45:44.170 align:middle line:90%
or which is the joy stone.

00:45:44.170 --> 00:45:47.060 align:middle line:84%
They all just hold
your essence for you.

00:45:47.060 --> 00:45:49.270 align:middle line:84%
And when you need to move
something like your grief,

00:45:49.270 --> 00:45:54.100 align:middle line:84%
just to get a little space,
you can blow it into a stone

00:45:54.100 --> 00:45:58.310 align:middle line:84%
and then put it on an altar, or
in your purse or on your desk.

00:45:58.310 --> 00:45:59.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Any stone.

00:45:59.110 --> 00:46:02.060 align:middle line:90%


00:46:02.060 --> 00:46:04.720 align:middle line:10%
>>EDWARDS: So that's
just a little part.

00:46:04.720 --> 00:46:07.900 align:middle line:84%
And rituals are easy
to create, but probably

00:46:07.900 --> 00:46:09.980 align:middle line:90%
a little forethought helps.

00:46:09.980 --> 00:46:10.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:46:10.780 --> 00:46:11.580 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Yes.

00:46:11.580 --> 00:46:13.660 align:middle line:90%
A little preparation.

00:46:13.660 --> 00:46:16.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It ceremonializes
something and gives it meaning.

00:46:16.760 --> 00:46:17.560 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Right.

00:46:17.560 --> 00:46:20.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it starts
the closure process.

00:46:20.150 --> 00:46:21.280 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Right.

00:46:21.280 --> 00:46:23.610 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Even if
there wasn't closure

00:46:23.610 --> 00:46:26.650 align:middle line:84%
in that situation with the
funeral of the suicide.

00:46:26.650 --> 00:46:29.983 align:middle line:84%
Did that family begin some type
of closure from that process?

00:46:29.983 --> 00:46:30.900 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: They began.

00:46:30.900 --> 00:46:31.730 align:middle line:90%
It's a long road.

00:46:31.730 --> 00:46:32.530 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:46:32.530 --> 00:46:36.160 align:middle line:10%
>>EDWARDS: But what happens
is you move the guilt

00:46:36.160 --> 00:46:38.380 align:middle line:10%
a little bit out of the way.

00:46:38.380 --> 00:46:42.160 align:middle line:84%
You move the things
that will stop you

00:46:42.160 --> 00:46:44.800 align:middle line:90%
from grieving ritually.

00:46:44.800 --> 00:46:45.610 align:middle line:90%
The anger.

00:46:45.610 --> 00:46:46.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yes.

00:46:46.410 --> 00:46:49.180 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: A lot of people are
angry when there's a suicide,

00:46:49.180 --> 00:46:51.470 align:middle line:84%
or feel guilty that they
didn't see it coming.

00:46:51.470 --> 00:46:52.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:46:52.270 --> 00:46:55.240 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: And those are
emotions that we want to move.

00:46:55.240 --> 00:46:59.770 align:middle line:84%
They're real, but we want to
move them so that the grief can

00:46:59.770 --> 00:47:03.220 align:middle line:90%
come in and be truly expressed.

00:47:03.220 --> 00:47:07.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How can we help
others like my mom, where

00:47:07.660 --> 00:47:13.000 align:middle line:84%
I want to help her grieve,
but yet she's not necessarily

00:47:13.000 --> 00:47:13.970 align:middle line:90%
ready for it right now?

00:47:13.970 --> 00:47:14.770 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Right.

00:47:14.770 --> 00:47:17.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: She's in the doing
of the memorial and all.

00:47:17.830 --> 00:47:18.910 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Right.

00:47:18.910 --> 00:47:20.815 align:middle line:10%
Everybody grieves differently.

00:47:20.815 --> 00:47:21.850 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: OK.

00:47:21.850 --> 00:47:26.080 align:middle line:10%
>>EDWARDS: Respect your mom, and
respect her grieving process.

00:47:26.080 --> 00:47:28.150 align:middle line:10%
It will be very different
six months from now,

00:47:28.150 --> 00:47:30.940 align:middle line:10%
when there's no plans
for a funeral or taking

00:47:30.940 --> 00:47:36.700 align:middle line:10%
care of the last will and
the estate, things like that.

00:47:36.700 --> 00:47:39.640 align:middle line:10%
Maybe share some rituals where
you and your mother can create.

00:47:39.640 --> 00:47:42.790 align:middle line:10%
Maybe going out on a
walk to a special place.

00:47:42.790 --> 00:47:43.850 align:middle line:10%
That's a ritual.

00:47:43.850 --> 00:47:44.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:47:44.650 --> 00:47:47.080 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: Going to
sit on a bench that's

00:47:47.080 --> 00:47:49.750 align:middle line:84%
a special place,
that's a ritual.

00:47:49.750 --> 00:47:52.250 align:middle line:10%
Make it a ritual
so that you do it.

00:47:52.250 --> 00:47:55.540 align:middle line:10%
And I always tell everyone,
on the anniversary

00:47:55.540 --> 00:47:58.630 align:middle line:10%
of your father's
death, plan ahead.

00:47:58.630 --> 00:47:59.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:47:59.440 --> 00:48:01.390 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: Have
a ritual in mind.

00:48:01.390 --> 00:48:05.770 align:middle line:84%
Even if you're by yourself,
be aware that the energy

00:48:05.770 --> 00:48:10.480 align:middle line:84%
that that anniversary can
really lay you low with grief.

00:48:10.480 --> 00:48:13.840 align:middle line:84%
So have a ritual in order
to expect the grief.

00:48:13.840 --> 00:48:16.910 align:middle line:84%
I know you're coming, so we're
going to celebrate together.

00:48:16.910 --> 00:48:17.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Like what?

00:48:17.710 --> 00:48:19.990 align:middle line:90%
What could we do?

00:48:19.990 --> 00:48:22.720 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: Well, I take a
three-day retreat on the--

00:48:22.720 --> 00:48:25.060 align:middle line:90%
my mother died on a Friday--

00:48:25.060 --> 00:48:28.350 align:middle line:84%
she went into a coma on
a Friday on her birthday,

00:48:28.350 --> 00:48:30.550 align:middle line:84%
and she died on a
Sunday, a three-day.

00:48:30.550 --> 00:48:33.730 align:middle line:84%
Every year, I take
a three-day retreat.

00:48:33.730 --> 00:48:35.950 align:middle line:90%
Nobody interferes with that.

00:48:35.950 --> 00:48:37.070 align:middle line:90%
No work.

00:48:37.070 --> 00:48:37.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Every year.

00:48:37.870 --> 00:48:39.440 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Every year.

00:48:39.440 --> 00:48:43.000 align:middle line:84%
And in the beginning, I would,
you know, talk to my mom,

00:48:43.000 --> 00:48:45.910 align:middle line:84%
and I'd read her journals,
and I'd put pictures up,

00:48:45.910 --> 00:48:47.870 align:middle line:90%
and I'd cook her favorite soup.

00:48:47.870 --> 00:48:48.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Aw.

00:48:48.670 --> 00:48:50.470 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: But
after 15 years now,

00:48:50.470 --> 00:48:53.150 align:middle line:84%
it's my mom coming
to take care of me.

00:48:53.150 --> 00:48:54.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:48:54.010 --> 00:48:55.960 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: I get to rest.

00:48:55.960 --> 00:48:59.540 align:middle line:84%
I get to do something, maybe
go get a manicure or something

00:48:59.540 --> 00:49:00.340 align:middle line:90%
fun.

00:49:00.340 --> 00:49:01.142 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:49:01.142 --> 00:49:02.350 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: And I hear my mom.

00:49:02.350 --> 00:49:04.640 align:middle line:90%
She's taking care of me now.

00:49:04.640 --> 00:49:05.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's amazing.

00:49:05.840 --> 00:49:07.220 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: So grief shifts.

00:49:07.220 --> 00:49:08.300 align:middle line:90%
It changes.

00:49:08.300 --> 00:49:10.760 align:middle line:90%
But it's our time together.

00:49:10.760 --> 00:49:15.950 align:middle line:84%
And people, because we think
we have to get over grief,

00:49:15.950 --> 00:49:19.170 align:middle line:90%
that's not true.

00:49:19.170 --> 00:49:22.650 align:middle line:84%
We don't get over grief,
we get better at it.

00:49:22.650 --> 00:49:26.630 align:middle line:84%
But we don't usually get
over a really important loss.

00:49:26.630 --> 00:49:31.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it's living
with dying and with grief.

00:49:31.190 --> 00:49:32.280 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Exactly.

00:49:32.280 --> 00:49:33.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Constantly.

00:49:33.080 --> 00:49:33.930 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't go away.

00:49:33.930 --> 00:49:34.730 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: No.

00:49:34.730 --> 00:49:39.500 align:middle line:84%
And our goal as an organization
is help people build resilience

00:49:39.500 --> 00:49:41.610 align:middle line:90%
while living with loss.

00:49:41.610 --> 00:49:43.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mhm.

00:49:43.050 --> 00:49:43.850 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:49:43.850 --> 00:49:47.570 align:middle line:84%
And there's a maternity
leave and a paternity leave,

00:49:47.570 --> 00:49:49.820 align:middle line:84%
but there's not necessarily
a grieving leave.

00:49:49.820 --> 00:49:50.660 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: No.

00:49:50.660 --> 00:49:51.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:49:51.740 --> 00:49:54.678 align:middle line:84%
For those of us that have
to get back to work, and--

00:49:54.678 --> 00:49:56.720 align:middle line:84%
although I love what I do
and this doesn't really

00:49:56.720 --> 00:49:59.745 align:middle line:84%
work for me, but it's actually
helpful for me to be here.

00:49:59.745 --> 00:50:00.620 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Of course.

00:50:00.620 --> 00:50:01.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, to do this.

00:50:01.850 --> 00:50:03.558 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: And get
back in your routines.

00:50:03.558 --> 00:50:06.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: To talk with people
like you, I mean, my goodness.

00:50:06.560 --> 00:50:08.030 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: How did this happen?

00:50:08.030 --> 00:50:10.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, because
we had this interview

00:50:10.490 --> 00:50:14.770 align:middle line:84%
scheduled several months before,
and it happened this time.

00:50:14.770 --> 00:50:15.980 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: Yeah.

00:50:15.980 --> 00:50:17.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What can people do?

00:50:17.180 --> 00:50:20.150 align:middle line:84%
I noticed that you have, you
know, Conscious Transitions,

00:50:20.150 --> 00:50:22.910 align:middle line:90%
you have a program, a workshop.

00:50:22.910 --> 00:50:26.060 align:middle line:84%
What is it that you teach,
or how do you take people

00:50:26.060 --> 00:50:27.320 align:middle line:90%
through this process?

00:50:27.320 --> 00:50:30.350 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: Well, we work a
lot with hospice workers,

00:50:30.350 --> 00:50:34.420 align:middle line:84%
medical workers, doctors,
nurses, psychiatrists.

00:50:34.420 --> 00:50:36.950 align:middle line:90%


00:50:36.950 --> 00:50:41.420 align:middle line:84%
We help them language death and
create a different relationship

00:50:41.420 --> 00:50:42.840 align:middle line:90%
with death.

00:50:42.840 --> 00:50:46.400 align:middle line:84%
We also work with
the general public,

00:50:46.400 --> 00:50:49.760 align:middle line:84%
helping them language
death in a different way.

00:50:49.760 --> 00:50:53.120 align:middle line:84%
Right now, we're running
a program this year

00:50:53.120 --> 00:50:58.100 align:middle line:84%
called Conscious Transitions,
Preparing Your Literal

00:50:58.100 --> 00:50:59.670 align:middle line:90%
Documents.

00:50:59.670 --> 00:51:01.190 align:middle line:10%
And this started in January.

00:51:01.190 --> 00:51:04.190 align:middle line:84%
I decided I was going to
get my documents rewritten.

00:51:04.190 --> 00:51:05.780 align:middle line:90%
They're getting sort of old.

00:51:05.780 --> 00:51:07.730 align:middle line:10%
And I thought,
well, I'm just going

00:51:07.730 --> 00:51:11.810 align:middle line:10%
to take all our subscribers
through with me.

00:51:11.810 --> 00:51:15.110 align:middle line:84%
And every month,
something appears.

00:51:15.110 --> 00:51:18.410 align:middle line:84%
So the first month, it was
just conversations about death.

00:51:18.410 --> 00:51:20.180 align:middle line:84%
And then a friend of
mine died, and I had

00:51:20.180 --> 00:51:21.500 align:middle line:90%
to help her in the hospital.

00:51:21.500 --> 00:51:24.230 align:middle line:10%
I was her medical agent.

00:51:24.230 --> 00:51:27.390 align:middle line:10%
And so the next month, I wrote
about you need a medical agent.

00:51:27.390 --> 00:51:29.140 align:middle line:84%
You need to appoint
someone who's strong--

00:51:29.140 --> 00:51:29.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You do.

00:51:29.400 --> 00:51:30.530 align:middle line:90%
>>EDWARDS: --and can help you.

00:51:30.530 --> 00:51:30.980 align:middle line:90%
And you need--

00:51:30.980 --> 00:51:31.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Can make
those decisions.

00:51:31.040 --> 00:51:32.240 align:middle line:84%
>>EDWARDS: --to tell
them what you want.

